## Implementation Checklist

### Before Any Color Change
- [ ] Check existing functionality works
- [ ] Verify text contrast ratios
- [ ] Test on mobile devices
- [ ] Validate with screen readers
- [ ] Check print styles

### After Color Implementation
- [ ] Run accessibility audit
- [ ] Test all interactive elements
- [ ] Verify hover/focus states
- [ ] Check loading states
- [ ] Validate across browsers

## Quality Gates

### Mandatory Checks
1. **Contrast Ratio**: Must meet WCAG AA standards
2. **Functionality**: No broken interactions
3. **Responsive**: Works on all screen sizes
4. **Performance**: No impact on load times
5. **Brand Consistency**: Follows SOI color hierarchy

### Review Criteria
- Does it enhance medical trust?
- Is text clearly readable?
- Do colors guide user journey?
- Are CTAs prominent but not overwhelming?
- Does it feel cohesive with existing brand?

## Emergency Rollback Plan
If any implementation causes:
- Accessibility issues
- Functionality breaks
- Performance degradation
- User experience problems

**Immediately revert** and document issues for resolution.